The paper discusses a file system design that incorporates both kernel and user-level components, which suggests it falls under the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on persistent memory, which is a topic covered in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also discusses data allocation and coordination, which are topics covered in the Databases (cs.DB) category. Finally, the paper discusses fine-grained write protection, which is a topic covered in the Architecture (cs.AR) category.
